Given a string s, find the length of the longest substring without duplicate characters.

Input: s = "abcabcbb"
Output: 3
Explanation: The answer is "abc", with the length of 3. Note that "bca" and "cab" are also correct answers.

Logic behind:
    character should not repeat , so keep the chracter in map, if exist then check the length of current substing 

    abc after that again a so substring abc have 3 length 
    use 2 pointers left and right for capturing the substring start and end

steps:
1. initilize left (start) , start and maxlength 
2. iterate string from 0 index to length as right (end )
3. check the character if it exist in map then update the value of left (starting) 
4. put the character in map with current index
5. start (right )- end  (left) = current length 
6. if max length less then update the maxlength and change the start to left in case if its udpated 
7. start , start+maxlength gives the index of subting start and end 

    

Solution:
class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLongestSubstring(String s) {
        AtomicInteger left = new AtomicInteger(0);
        AtomicInteger start = new AtomicInteger(0);
        AtomicInteger maxLength = new AtomicInteger(0);
        Map<Character,Integer> map= new HashMap <> ();
        IntStream.range(0, s.length()).forEach(
            right -> {
            char ch = s.charAt(right);

            if(map.containsKey(ch)){
              left.set(Math.max(left.get(), map.get(ch)+1)); 
            }
            map.put(ch,right);
            int currentLen = right - left.get() +1;

            if(currentLen > maxLength.get()){
                maxLength.set(currentLen);
                start.set(left.get());
            }
            }
            
        );

        return maxLength.get();
        
    }
}
